The phrase **"every 12°C, the digits are inverted"** is a **mnemonic trick** to help remember how to convert Celsius (°C) to Fahrenheit (°F) for **whole numbers** where the Celsius temperature is a two-digit number (e.g., 10°C, 20°C, 30°C, etc.).

